Windows toolset:
1. download mingw64 with posix support 
2. add <mingw64 path>/bin to PATH

Boost: 
1. download boost 1.60.0
2. cd boost_1.60.0/tools/build/
3. bootstrap.sh mingw
4. cd boost_1.60.0
5. tools/build/b2.exe --prefix=<destination path> toolset=gcc target-os=windows link=static runtime-link=static architecture=x86 address-model=64 threading=multi

Xcerces:
1. download xerces-c-3.1.1
2. unzip xerces to msys64 and get into the path xerces-c-3.1.1
3. use the configuration below, `--disable-sse2` may be removed
4. ./configure host=x86_64-w64-mingw64 build=x86_64-w64-mingw64 CFLAGS=-O3 CXXFLAGS=-O3 --prefix=<the path you want to save the include and lib of xerces> --disable-sse2
5. cd src;make clean;make

Xalan:
1. export XERCESCROOT=<path>/proteomics_cpp/thirdparty/xerces-c-3.1.1/
2. export XALANCROOT=<path>/proteomics_cpp/thirdparty/xalan-c-1.11/c/
3. ./runConfigure -p mingw-msys -c gcc -x g++ -r none -z -march=athlon64 -z -m64
4. edit `src/xalanc/Makefile` 
5. edit `src/xalanc/Utils/XalanMsgLig/Makefile`
6. edit `Makefile.incl` and remove `/` in prefix, see the `Makefile` in the directory
7. make 
8. make install

Proteomics Wizards
1. download TPP 4.8.0
2. cp pwiz directory to src/pwiz 
2. cp library/boost_aux/ to src/pwiz/boost 

Download links:

1. mingw64 (x86_64-4.8.2-release-posix-seh-rt_v3-rev4.7z): http://sourceforge.net/projects/mingw-w64/files/Toolchains%20targetting%20Win64/Personal%20Builds/mingw-builds/4.8.2/threads-posix/seh/
2. msys64: http://sourceforge.net/projects/msys2/files/Base/x86_64/msys2-x86_64-20140910.exe
3. boost (boost_1_60_0.zip): https://sourceforge.net/projects/boost/files/boost/1.60.0/
4. xerces-c (xerces-c-3.1.1.zip): http://xerces.apache.org/xerces-c/download.cgi
5. xalan (xalan_c-1.11-src.zip): http://xalan.apache.org/xalan-c/download.html
